<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-353-740  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 353 740.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>CommunicationsWeek  April 16 1990 n296 p50(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Connecticut building state net: to link state's cities andregions. (Public Networking)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Schultz, Beth.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The state of Connecticut's Office of Information and Technology isdeveloping a strategic plan for the provision of a backbonenetwork to handle the state's future telecommunications traffic.andO;The planners will utilize the technology available on the publicswitched network.andP;  Currently, 52.9 percent of the state's $32million telecommunications budget goes to Southern New EnglandTelephone CO (New Haven, CT).andP;  The objective of the planning willbe to establish a communications infrastructure that will allowthe full implementation of integrated voice and data services.andP;  Anumber of strategies will be employed, including the use ofestablished technologies whenever feasible, the use of de factostandards, digital technology and integrated voice and dataservice across fiber optic transmission media.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Southern New England Telephone Co. (communication systems).andO;Topic:     ConnecticutTelephone SystemsTelecommunicationsStrategic PlanningBackbone NetworksDigital CommunicationsFiber Optics.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>